<TITLE> Doctors urged to take up district level posts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  Health minister Dr A F M Ruhal Haque has urged doctors to get rid of their city-oriented mentality and go to places outside big cities so that nearly 5000 vacant posts at the district and sub-district level can be filled up. He made the comments Thursday morning while inaugurating a national scientific conference and participating in the 37th anniversary of the Obstetrical and Gynaecological Society of Bangladesh, which was held at the Bangabandhu International Conference Centre. Dr Haq he also said that if these posts were taken up, the health care problem in the country would be greatly reduced. He added that the new health policy would be finalised shortly. OGSB president Professor Sayeba Akther and OGSB general secretary Professor Shah Alam spoke at the conference. bd
